The paper deals with the computational design and fabrication of parquetry, which involves the use of textures and patterns to create a decorative surface. This falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV), as the authors use image synthesis and stylization techniques to create the parquetry designs. Additionally, the use of algorithms to efficiently solve the combinatorial problem of finding optimal parts and avoiding resource collisions suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the use of wood veneer as a material for the parquetry suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM), as the authors may explore the use of other materials in future work.
